                            <comment id="277287" author="zam" created="Wed, 12 Aug 2020 09:22:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;recently seen not in interopt testing : &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/2a65106b-6525-459b-9933-f0548ebaf4e1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/2a65106b-6525-459b-9933-f0548ebaf4e1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="256628" author="adilger" created="Fri, 18 Oct 2019 06:15:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems likely that this is caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11426&quot; title=&quot;2/2 Olafs agree: changelog entries are emitted out of order&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11426&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11426&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; problems with ChangeLog records being skipped on the 2.10.8 server. There is only a single file difference in the target copy, which seems similar to that problem. If there was a serious problem, it would have had dozens of files different as is typically seen with lustre_rsync problems. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
